sub_title: Educational Counselor / Project Manager @ NIECC | Education Development
summary:
With over 9 years of experience in the education sector, I am a passionate and driven international project manager and counselor at NIECC, a company that offers innovative and impactful educational and cultural exchange programs for students and young professionals from diverse backgrounds and disciplines.

My core competencies include problem solving, communication, and customer relationship management, which enable me to oversee projects from inception to completion, ensure high-quality outcomes, and build strong stakeholder relationships. As a registered urbanist with a master's degree in urbanism from Delft University of Technology, I also bring domain expertise and intercultural competency to my role, as I design and facilitate programs that foster learning and exchange on urban issues and challenges.
